headline: Tariffs Make Competition Tougher for a Georgia Tractor Maker
summary: Agco for years has been trying to boost its business in the U.S., where it has held the No. 3 spot in essentially a three-company farm-equipment market.  The Duluth, Ga., company doesn’t have enough U.S. sales to justify moving more production out of Europe, where it has most of its production and sales, Chief Financial Officer Damon Audia said.  Meanwhile, in Europe, where much of its supply chain and sales are aligned, the company could see a boost by avoiding many tariff costs that its peers Deere & Co. and CNH Industrial face.

summary: When Wall Street turns bearish on a stock, it’s worth paying attention. These calls stand out because analysts rarely issue grim ratings on companies for fear their firms will lose out in other business lines such as M&A advisory.

headline: Coastline Equipment Named Newest Trimble Technology Outlet
summary: Trimble® (Nasdaq: TRMB) today announced Coastline Equipment as the newest Trimble Technology Outlet. Based in Long Beach, California, Coastline will now sell Trimble grade control, site positioning systems and correction services technology directly to customers using John Deere and Hamm earthmoving equipment.
